The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 28: The rate of inflation rose to 3.55 per cent for the week ended April 15, from 3.24 per cent in the previous week mainly due to costlier manufactured and non-food items. Wholesale prices rose 3.55 per cent as aviation fuel also became costlier; but inflation was lower than 5.91 per cent in the year-ago period. 

 Calcutta, April 28: Tata Steel has acquired a 67.11 per cent stake in Millennium Steel Public Company of Thailand for about $170 million. The stake was acquired through a combination of preferential allotment of 24.99 per cent and an open offer of 42.12 per cent. 

 New Delhi, April 28: Telecom tribunal TDSAT has decided to hear all three petitions against Trai filed by BSNL and COAI collectively on May 26. BSNL and the Cellular Operators Association of India has challenged the telecom regulator on differential tarrifs, qualitative service norms and interconnectivity.

 New Delhi, April 28: TVS Motor will set up a motorcycle assembly plant in Columbia through a joint venture company with a local partner. ?We plan to enter into a joint venture with a Columbian partner for setting up an assembly plant in that country,? a company official said from Chennai.

 New Delhi, April 28: Petronet LNG will raise $100 million through issue of foreign currency convertible bonds in June-July.




